    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "$a \\divides b$ means $b = ak$ for some integer $k$.",
        "**Division algorithm**: $a = dq + r$ with $0 \\leq r < d$.",
        "A **prime** has no divisors except 1 and itself.",
        "**Fundamental Theorem**: Every integer $> 1$ has a unique \n prime factorization.",
        "$\\gcd(a, b)$ is the largest common divisor; $\\lcm(a, b)$ is the \n smallest common multiple.",
        "**Euclidean algorithm**: $\\gcd(a, b) = \\gcd(b, a \\mod b)$.",
        "**Bézout's identity**: $\\gcd(a, b) = as + bt$ for some \n integers $s, t$.",
        "$a \\equiv b \\pmod{m}$ means $m \\divides (a - b)$.",
        "**Fermat's Little Theorem**: $a^{p-1} \\equiv 1 \\pmod{p}$ for \n prime $p$, $\\gcd(a, p) = 1$.",
        "**RSA cryptography** uses modular exponentiation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Important Formulas"
    },
    {
